01:01:26.072 --> 01:01:29.428
- Are you kidding or what?
- It is I who ordered those curtains...

934
01:01:29.592 --> 01:01:34.586
...and every lick of furniture in here and
this bed you sleep in with that bitch!

935
01:01:34.792 --> 01:01:38.751
Sit on the bed. shut your mouth
or so help me. l'll hit you with this chair.

936
01:01:38.952 --> 01:01:41.022
That is a table!

937
01:01:42.432 --> 01:01:43.501
Okay?

938
01:01:43.672 --> 01:01:45.822
How could you do it?

939
01:01:46.192 --> 01:01:50.151
How could you move
another woman into my home?

940
01:01:50.512 --> 01:01:52.867
What happened to Larry. Gloria?
He dump you?

941
01:01:53.032 --> 01:01:56.991
No! No. he most certainly
did not dump me.

942
01:01:57.192 --> 01:01:59.422
Oh. no? So. what's the deal here?

943
01:01:59.592 --> 01:02:04.268
You walk out on me. not eight weeks
ago. Gloria. 11 weeks ago.

944
01:02:05.072 --> 01:02:07.791
A whole season of the
year has passed.

945
01:02:07.992 --> 01:02:12.383
It was fall. with football in it.
It is now winter. with hockey in it.

946
01:02:13.992 --> 01:02:17.701
Gloria. answer me.
Gloria. what is going on?

947
01:02:19.592 --> 01:02:21.787
I don't know.

948
01:02:24.472 --> 01:02:27.703
I don't know.
I'm so confused.

949
01:02:29.392 --> 01:02:32.190
You could drive me crazy.
you know that? Really crazy.

950
01:02:35.072 --> 01:02:37.632
Larry is a wonderful man.

951
01:02:38.472 --> 01:02:43.023
- I'm thrilled to hear this.
- A wonderful man. but he's not you.

952
01:02:44.272 --> 01:02:48.868
I figured that when he scratched his leg
and I felt nothing. I said. "He's not me."

953
01:02:49.912 --> 01:02:52.710
How can you joke at a time like this?

954
01:02:52.872 --> 01:02:57.104
I joke. you sob. what difference
does it make? We're both miserable.

955
01:02:58.792 --> 01:03:00.589
Oh. Ivan.

956
01:03:00.752 --> 01:03:04.586
Iv�n. I miss you.
I miss the family.

957
01:03:04.752 --> 01:03:09.667
I miss the bickering and the sprouts
and the toilet seat up.

958
01:03:09.872 --> 01:03:13.467
- I miss it. I miss it.
- I knew you would.

959
01:03:18.752 --> 01:03:19.787
Um...

960
01:03:23.312 --> 01:03:26.270
- Are you in love with this woman?
- With Alice?

961
01:03:27.312 --> 01:03:32.261
No. No. with Sy Peck. the Arts and
Leisure editor of the Sunday Times.

962
01:03:32.472 --> 01:03:34.269
That was funny.

963
01:03:34.432 --> 01:03:37.902
- Are you?
- No.

964
01:03:41.352 --> 01:03:44.344
I do not love Alice Detroit.

965
01:03:45.752 --> 01:03:50.030
I did not actually conceptualize
that fact till this very moment.

966
01:03:50.192 --> 01:03:53.343
No. I love you.

967
01:03:56.472 --> 01:04:00.909
Gloria. I miss you and our family
so much I could vomit.

968
01:04:04.872 --> 01:04:07.432
I'd take you back in a minute. Gloria.

969
01:04:07.792 --> 01:04:09.430
Not too many questions asked.

970
01:04:11.552 --> 01:04:15.943
Larry and I are moving to the
Good Harbor Beach Inn in Massachusetts.

971
01:04:16.152 --> 01:04:19.110
We're there for a three-month trial
and if it works...

972
01:04:19.272 --> 01:04:22.548
...we'll be married
on Larry's birthday in March.

973
01:04:32.312 --> 01:04:34.064
Okay.

974
01:04:36.032 --> 01:04:40.025
Okay. I guess I should get
back to rehearsal.

975
01:04:40.472 --> 01:04:43.305
Enough taking time off
from work for fun.

976
01:04:45.112 --> 01:04:48.661
- You can keep the night table. Gloria.
- No.

977
01:04:51.552 --> 01:04:55.306
I just wanna say that you are
the craziest person l've seen today...

978
01:04:55.472 --> 01:04:57.622
...since the guy blocking the bank door.

979
01:04:57.792 --> 01:05:03.105
He was wearing a Superman cape
and pantyhose. Crazier than you.

980
01:05:03.712 --> 01:05:05.430
Maybe not.

981
01:05:07.912 --> 01:05:11.427
"Object of the language conversion
sack is to immerse the student..."

982
01:05:11.592 --> 01:05:13.662
- I mean. is it boring?
Lvan.

983
01:05:13.832 --> 01:05:17.871
Iv�n. there's no other way to say this.
we are in trouble in the second act.

984
01:05:18.032 --> 01:05:21.308
I can't do the fakakta speech.
I sound like Richard Nixon.

985
01:05:21.472 --> 01:05:23.383
Can we talk alone?
- The play dies.

986
01:05:23.552 --> 01:05:27.067
We need something funny or visual.
We're going along. It's sailing.

987
01:05:27.232 --> 01:05:28.790
Then suddenly it stops. It's dead.

988
01:05:28.952 --> 01:05:30.749
- Will you excuse us?
- What are you...?

989
01:05:30.912 --> 01:05:34.825
But l'm standing up here making a fool
out of myself. I need help from you.

990
01:05:35.392 --> 01:05:37.348
Excuse us a minute. Morris. please.

991
01:05:37.512 --> 01:05:40.743
- But where are you...?
- Iv�n. when do I get the rewrite?

992
01:05:40.912 --> 01:05:43.551
You get it soon. I promise you.
I promise you.

993
01:05:43.712 --> 01:05:47.341
- Are you coming back?
Yeah. l'll see you later.

994
01:05:49.192 --> 01:05:51.467
- Are the kids okay?
- Yeah.

995
01:05:53.712 --> 01:05:57.625
Alice. if I asked you to move out.
would you quit the play?

996
01:05:58.072 --> 01:06:02.270
If you asked me to move out.
would I quit the play?

997
01:06:09.992 --> 01:06:12.665
- No. I would not leave the play.
- You wouldn't?

998
01:06:12.832 --> 01:06:15.744
No. I would not.

999
01:06:16.712 --> 01:06:18.748
Oh. Ivan.

1000
01:06:19.592 --> 01:06:23.062
I'd be so relieved to move out.
Really. don't you know that?

1001
01:06:23.232 --> 01:06:24.665
You wouldn't hate me?

1002
01:06:24.832 --> 01:06:27.824
No. No.

1003
01:06:28.112 --> 01:06:30.626
No. I wouldn't hate you.
I'm crazy about you.

1004
01:06:30.952 --> 01:06:33.022
Why. Alice?
Is something wrong with you?

1005
01:06:33.192 --> 01:06:34.864
Yeah.

1006
01:06:36.472 --> 01:06:39.862
"Alice doesn't live here anymore"?
Don't you think that's funny?

1007
01:06:40.512 --> 01:06:42.821
I myself never saw the movie.
I don't know.

1008
01:06:43.232 --> 01:06:45.462
I'm still hung up on your mother. kid.

1009
01:06:45.912 --> 01:06:47.504
Who. my mother or his mother?

1010
01:06:48.472 --> 01:06:49.791
His mother.

1011
01:06:49.952 --> 01:06:52.944
I gotta do rewrites.
Hold the fort. all right?

1012
01:08:00.552 --> 01:08:02.190
Hello.

1013
01:08:02.512 --> 01:08:04.309
Hello?

1014
01:08:04.592 --> 01:08:06.822
- Hello. is somebody there?
Who is it. Gloria?

1015
01:08:06.992 --> 01:08:08.550
Hello.

1016
01:08:08.712 --> 01:08:11.545
- Jesus. I really hate that.
What's the matter?

1017
01:08:11.712 --> 01:08:15.102
Some damn pervert calling. breathing.

1018
01:08:15.952 --> 01:08:19.103
Okay. you have a good day.

1019
01:08:35.952 --> 01:08:39.501
Hi. I'm from troop 638
and l'm selling Girl Scout cookies.

1020
01:08:40.472 --> 01:08:43.111
Well. l'm gonna be writing
the second act now.

1021
01:08:43.312 --> 01:08:47.510
We are not going to read it
again. We've read through it 10 times!

1022
01:08:47.672 --> 01:08:51.301
It makes no sense. It doesn't work!
Did you hear it?

1023
01:08:51.472 --> 01:08:53.064
Morris. you're screaming at me.

1024
01:08:53.272 --> 01:08:57.629
Yes. I am screaming! I waited two weeks
for a goddamn rewrite.

1025
01:08:57.792 --> 01:09:00.431
And when I get it.
it worsens the problem.

1026
01:09:00.592 --> 01:09:03.060
No. No. Ivan. it doesn't worsen
the problem.

1027
01:09:03.232 --> 01:09:05.700
It doesn't even address the problem.

1028
01:09:05.872 --> 01:09:09.660
Have you ever read English With Tears
by Ivan Travalian?

1029
01:09:09.832 --> 01:09:13.745
I wonder. because these pages
are not germane!

1030
01:09:15.672 --> 01:09:18.232
I've been a little flaky lately.
I've been...

1031
01:09:18.392 --> 01:09:19.825
A little flaky?

1032
01:09:20.032 --> 01:09:23.945
You are doing everything within your
power to sink and submerge this ship.

1033
01:09:24.112 --> 01:09:26.910
- I'm not going down with you!
- That's your attitude?

1034
01:09:27.072 --> 01:09:29.028
Either you come up with a rewrite...

1035
01:09:29.192 --> 01:09:33.231
Excuse me. But this is most
embarrassing for all of us up here.

1036
01:09:33.392 --> 01:09:39.388
So we are going home until
tomorrow. right? Till tomorrow.

1037
01:09:53.632 --> 01:09:58.547
Hey! Hey. hello?
Hey. Hey. hey. l'm the father.

1038
01:09:58.712 --> 01:10:01.021
- You're Ivan Travalian?
- Yeah. why?

1039
01:10:01.232 --> 01:10:04.907
Show him the picture. Kapinsky.
You know these two kids. Mr. Travalian?

1040
01:10:07.792 --> 01:10:09.908
There's no two girls in this house.

1041
01:10:10.112 --> 01:10:12.910
We would never hide two girls
in this house.

1042
01:10:13.472 --> 01:10:16.145
We didn't even think he'd notice
we were gone.

1043
01:10:16.312 --> 01:10:19.429
Are we gonna go to jail?
I'm not gonna cry!

1044
01:10:19.592 --> 01:10:22.390
Come on. Bon.
You're not gonna go to jail.

1045
01:10:23.392 --> 01:10:26.702
I mean. this is reasonably explainable.
Lieutenant Kapinsky.

1046
01:10:26.872 --> 01:10:28.942
He's Kapinsky.
I'm Lieutenant Glass.

1047
01:10:29.192 --> 01:10:33.265
Okay. What if I were to keep them
for a couple of days?

1048
01:10:33.432 --> 01:10:36.185
Just a week. I know their dad.
I've talked to him.

1049
01:10:36.352 --> 01:10:38.024
No way. Look. Mr. Travalian.

1050
01:10:38.192 --> 01:10:42.788
I got a father and a detective filling out
papers. I gotta hand the kids over first.

1051
01:10:42.952 --> 01:10:46.865
Then you work it out between you.
l'm all for that. I got kids of my own.

1052
01:10:47.032 --> 01:10:48.909
I'm not married.

1053
01:10:50.512 --> 01:10:53.902
Policemen are doing their job. doll.
You gotta go to your dad...

1054
01:10:54.112 --> 01:10:56.785
- No!
- It's unfair. He doesn't want us. anyway.

1055
01:10:56.952 --> 01:11:00.706
Come on. Deb. He's gone through
a lot of trouble to bring you back.

1056
01:11:00.912 --> 01:11:04.188
Only because he's suing Gloria
to stop the support payments.

1057
01:11:04.352 --> 01:11:07.310
What?
- That's the truth.

1058
01:11:14.432 --> 01:11:18.311
Lieutenant Glass and Officer Kapinsky
are just doing what they gotta...

1059
01:11:18.472 --> 01:11:19.871
But. Ivan. I don't wanna g...

1060
01:11:20.032 --> 01:11:21.260
Shh. Shh. Shh.

1061
01:11:22.512 --> 01:11:25.470
You're gonna go upstairs now.
We'll pack our suitcases.

1062
01:11:25.632 --> 01:11:28.271
We're gonna leave for Greenwich
tonight with Dad.

1063
01:11:28.432 --> 01:11:31.663
Tomorrow I call him on the phone.
maybe a couple of days.

1064
01:11:31.832 --> 01:11:35.507
I wait until things calm down
a little. Okay?

1065
01:11:35.712 --> 01:11:38.943
- Why can't they stay with us. damn it?
- Geraldo. go practice.

1066
01:11:39.152 --> 01:11:41.268
I don't wanna practice.

1067
01:11:42.752 --> 01:11:45.107
Okay. okay.

1068
01:11:46.472 --> 01:11:48.110
Hang tough.

1069
01:11:48.312 --> 01:11:52.703
Okay. you guys. come on.
Let's go upstairs and pack. Come on.

1070
01:11:52.872 --> 01:11:55.944
- There's more Cokes in the fridge. okay?
- Hey. no sweat.

1071
01:11:56.112 --> 01:11:58.990
We'll make it snappy.
- They're really cute.

1072
01:12:02.472 --> 01:12:05.032
Okay. okay.
Let's go. Let's go. Let's go!

1073
01:12:05.192 --> 01:12:07.626
Where we going?
- We're making a break for it.

1074
01:12:07.792 --> 01:12:10.784
Easy. easy. easy. Let's go.
Come on.

1075
01:12:12.552 --> 01:12:14.861
Where are we going?
To the roof.

1076
01:12:15.032 --> 01:12:17.262
To the roof?
Why are we going to the roof?

1077
01:12:17.472 --> 01:12:20.145
I'm not giving you
over to the cops or your father.

1078
01:12:20.312 --> 01:12:21.427
You're not going back...

1079
01:12:21.632 --> 01:12:25.591
- Rotten child support payments...
Come on. will you hurry?

1080
01:12:30.912 --> 01:12:35.463
I don't like this. I don't like this.
- This is crazy.

1081
01:12:36.032 --> 01:12:39.945
- Think something's weird. Kapinsky.
- Think maybe they just like salads?

1082
01:12:40.912 --> 01:12:42.550
Come on. let's go.

1083
01:12:42.752 --> 01:12:44.549
Hurry up.
Let's go.

1084
01:12:44.752 --> 01:12:49.064
Where are you climbing?
Will you hurry?

1085
01:12:49.272 --> 01:12:52.628
You're stepping on my fingers.
I'm not.

1086
01:12:52.792 --> 01:12:57.786
Exactly. you're stepping on it.
- Christ. l'll bet we're trapped.

1087
01:12:59.152 --> 01:13:00.631
Help me. Stop. that tickles.

1088
01:13:00.792 --> 01:13:02.703
You want me
to pull you by your hair?

1089
01:13:04.512 --> 01:13:06.582
This must be 1000 feet.
Okay.

1090
01:13:06.752 --> 01:13:09.505
After 90. it doesn't matter.
I'm gonna faint.

1091
01:13:09.672 --> 01:13:11.424
How do you get off this thing?

1092
01:13:11.592 --> 01:13:12.820
I knew it!

1093
01:13:13.032 --> 01:13:15.910
You're not gonna go
back to Greenwich. I'll find a way.

1094
01:13:16.072 --> 01:13:18.825
Great choices: Boring
Greenwich or violent death.

1095
01:13:18.992 --> 01:13:21.460
There's no way off this roof.
Shut up.

1096
01:13:21.672 --> 01:13:23.025
Pop. over here!

1097
01:13:23.752 --> 01:13:26.505
I knew it.
What if the cops find us?

1098
01:13:27.872 --> 01:13:30.864
We treated them decent.
- They can bust us down for this.

1099
01:13:31.032 --> 01:13:34.468
You wanna slip into a loincloth
and swing across to St. Vincent's?

1100
01:13:34.632 --> 01:13:37.021
Great. I'm facing
75 years for kidnapping...

1101
01:13:37.192 --> 01:13:39.786
...and l'm trapped on a roof
with Henny Youngman.

1102
01:13:47.872 --> 01:13:51.751
Travalian! Damn it. Travalian!
- He's making a fool of us. Kapinsky.

1103
01:13:52.032 --> 01:13:53.067
Okay.

1104
01:13:53.232 --> 01:13:56.463
I think I hear the cops.
Oh. God. can they get up here at us?

1105
01:13:56.672 --> 01:13:59.789
I hear them up there.
They're definitely on the roof.

1106
01:13:59.952 --> 01:14:02.466
Yeah. I hear them.
I can hear them.

1107
01:14:02.672 --> 01:14:04.344
What have I done?

1108
01:14:05.072 --> 01:14:08.064
They've got it jammed shut.
Let me give it a shove.

1109
01:14:08.272 --> 01:14:12.550
Forget it! No more Mr. Nice Guy.
I'll lock this bastard up for this.

1110
01:14:15.992 --> 01:14:17.869
Now what?!

1111
01:14:20.472 --> 01:14:25.592
Tell the sergeant to get the squad car
and the kids' father over here right away.

1112
01:14:26.992 --> 01:14:28.710
Lvan.

1113
01:14:29.712 --> 01:14:32.306
- Iv�n Travalian.
Lt's Daddy. That's Daddy.

1114
01:14:32.472 --> 01:14:36.101
Lt's me. Roger. Roger Slessinger.

1115
01:14:36.472 --> 01:14:38.428
Oh. my God.
They got us surrounded.

1116
01:14:38.632 --> 01:14:40.145
What do you see?
What?

1117
01:14:40.312 --> 01:14:42.701
Our picture
on page six of the New York Post.

1118
01:14:42.872 --> 01:14:44.828
I have done
something really crazy.

1119
01:14:45.032 --> 01:14:48.786
Look. Ivan. l'm down here on the
street with a bunch of cops.

1120
01:14:49.312 --> 01:14:51.906
Or police officers.

1121
01:14:52.752 --> 01:14:58.065
This is embarrassing. For God's sake.
send Debbie and Bonnie down here.

1122
01:14:58.952 --> 01:15:03.946
The cops think you may be doing
something sexual with them.

1123
01:15:04.752 --> 01:15:07.710
That is about the sickest
thing l've ever heard. Roger.

1124
01:15:07.872 --> 01:15:11.990
I've heard many sick things in my life.
I'm a playwright. for God's sake.

1125
01:15:12.152 --> 01:15:16.145
I didn 't suggest that. Iv�n.
The cops did.

1126
01:15:17.472 --> 01:15:19.702
Hey. this is Lieutenant Glass.

1127
01:15:19.912 --> 01:15:22.551
Mr. Travalian.
you'd better show the little girls.

1128
01:15:22.752 --> 01:15:25.744
Oh. my God. What have I done?
What have I done?

1129
01:15:25.952 --> 01:15:28.341
This is great. threats.
You know what's next?

1130
01:15:28.512 --> 01:15:32.630
They'll come at us from St. Vincent's
with Sten guns. Maybe napalm.

1131
01:15:33.112 --> 01:15:36.582
Daddy. Daddy. Don't shoot anybody.
We're fine. We're okay.

1132
01:15:36.792 --> 01:15:40.580
That's Debbie.
Where's your sister?

1133
01:15:41.352 --> 01:15:43.912
- She's right here.
- Come on. Bon. Show yourself.

1134
01:15:44.072 --> 01:15:45.471
They probably won't shoot.

1135
01:15:45.632 --> 01:15:50.069
This isn't fair. We're not supposed to go
to Connecticut. Mommy won us in court.

1136
01:15:50.232 --> 01:15:52.507
- What? What?
- I said. this isn't fair.

1137
01:15:52.672 --> 01:15:55.232
Mommy won us in court. not him.

1138
01:15:55.392 --> 01:15:58.464
She speaks the truth.
The kid speaks the truth.

1139
01:15:58.632 --> 01:16:00.065
Okay.

1140
01:16:00.672 --> 01:16:04.824
The mother of these girls
has legal custody.

1141
01:16:05.672 --> 01:16:09.870
That man does not have legal custody
over these two little girls.

1142
01:16:10.032 --> 01:16:12.262
- Can you follow my message?
Come on. Ivan.

1143
01:16:12.432 --> 01:16:16.744
You know as well as I do
that bitch has no rights. Not anymore.

1144
01:16:16.952 --> 01:16:20.228
Gloria Travalian.
the mother of these girls...

1145
01:16:20.392 --> 01:16:22.826
...among others.
who is also my wife...

1146
01:16:22.992 --> 01:16:27.144
...has legal custody over these girls.
I won't give them to that man there...

1147
01:16:27.352 --> 01:16:30.310
...who does not have legal custody.

1148
01:16:30.792 --> 01:16:34.501
And that is why we're all
huddled up here on the roof...

1149
01:16:34.672 --> 01:16:37.266
...as though we were acting
in a Fellini film.

1150
01:16:37.592 --> 01:16:40.823
What's he talking about?
- Mafia connections?

1151
01:16:40.992 --> 01:16:43.870
Come on. Ivan.

1152
01:16:46.392 --> 01:16:49.225
- I hope what he's saying isn't...
- Don't be ridiculous.

1153
01:16:49.552 --> 01:16:54.501
Who's got legal custody of the girls.
Mr. Slessinger? You or the missus?

1154
01:16:55.992 --> 01:16:57.664
Lt's a little complicated.

1155
01:16:57.872 --> 01:17:02.263
This is just a formality. Mr. Travalian. It
covers you just as much as it covers us.

1156
01:17:02.432 --> 01:17:03.421
I'm sure it does.

1157
